# Plot

This directory contains visualization scripts and notebooks used to analyze the numerical simulation results.

The plotting utilities generate publication-quality figures that illustrate the evolution of important physical quantities throughout the simulation. These visualizations facilitate interpretation, validation, and presentation of the computational results.

Typical outputs include:

- Time-dependent variable plots
- Radius evolution
- Temperature profiles
- Mass and evaporation dynamics
- Comparative analysis between simulation cases

The plotting scripts are independent from the numerical solver and are intended for post-processing the generated datasets.
